-- Finance Ministry Waives Taxes on Land Used for Public Housing for 3 Years
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-09-28T09:19:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-28/finance-ministry-waives-taxes-on-land-used-for-public-housing-for-3-years.html
China will waive taxes on land used
for public rent housing, the Ministry of Finance said in a
statement on its website today.  The ruling will take effect today and will last for three
years, according to the statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stanley James at 
 sjames8@bloomberg.net  